Title: The Library of Bootlegs | Four Corners Books
Description: In the depths of the British Library Sound Archive lies a wonderful treasure trove of illicit audio recordings . Such bootlegs are rock’n’roll relics of the pre-Internet age, perhaps only valued now by collectors . The audio they contain, once highly prized and difficult  'Trade Mark of Quality' (TMQ) label began to pump out a steady stream of concert recordings by the big rock bands of the era . TMQ’s ‘Live'r Than You'll Ever Be’ is said to have sold over 250,000  All of the big British artists of the day were bootlegged – often by outfits based abroad like TMQ . Records would be pressed abroad because the legal consequences were less significant . But, with the coming of punk, a homegrown bootleg culture really got going in the UK .  Bootlegs of forbidden music cut onto X-ray film in Cold War era Soviet Union .
